article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 65, N. Iowa 63
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Anthony Hill scored 17 points and Milwaukee beat Northern Iowa 65-63 Saturday. Milwaukee's (3-2) game-winning bucket came on a Tone Boyle jumper with two seconds left in the game. Milwaukee was leading by two points when UNI's (1-2) Anthony James scored on a fast break, tying the game at 61 with 1:49 to go. Milwaukee's Ryan Allen made a free throw at 35 seconds, followed by another free throw from Kaylon Williams with 16 seconds left. Kerwin Dunham then went 2 of 2 from the line for NIU, tying the game at 63 with the clock still at 16. Milwaukee was able to hang on until Boyle's jumper. Hill finished with four assists and eight rebounds, and Boyle had 12 points and two rebounds. Lonnie Boga added 10 points, eight rebounds and two steals. Kwadzo Ahelegbe had 14 points, five rebounds and three assists for NIU. Lucas O'Rear added 11 points and six rebounds.
